# Handle Ctrl+C gracefully in interactive prompts

## Context

Any script using readline for interactive prompts must handle SIGINT

## Pattern

Add SIGINT handler to readline interface that closes properly and exits cleanly. Prevents terminal from staying in raw mode after Ctrl+C.

## Example

```typescript
const rl = readline.createInterface({ input, output });
rl.on('SIGINT', () => {
  rl.close();
  console.log('\nCancelled.');
  process.exit(0);
});
```

## Why

Without SIGINT handling, Ctrl+C during a prompt can leave terminal corrupted, requiring user to kill the terminal window.
